# Global Coastal Hazard AI (Prithvi-100M)

End-to-end starter pipeline for flood mapping and resilience reporting using:
- Microsoft Planetary Computer (Sentinel-2 L2A via STAC)
- NASA/IBM Prithvi foundation model (segmentation checkpoint)
- FastAPI for production API serving

Target case study:
- Event: Cyclone Remal, Bangladesh, May 2024
- Bounding box: `[88.5, 21.5, 89.5, 22.8]`

---

## 1) Environment Setup (Windows / PowerShell)

### 1.1 Install prerequisites
1. Install Python 3.10+.
2. Install Git for Windows.
3. Optional but recommended: install [GitHub CLI](https://cli.github.com/).

### 1.2 Create and activate virtual environment
From project root:

```powershell
python -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
python -m pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install -e .
```

If script execution is blocked:

```powershell
Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope CurrentUser RemoteSigned
```

