## 6) Git + GitHub (Detailed)

### 6.1 Initialize repo
```powershell
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial Global Coastal Hazard AI pipeline with Prithvi + API"
```

### 6.2 Create `.gitignore`
Recommended contents:

```gitignore
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
.DS_Store
*.ipynb_checkpoints
```

### 6.3 Create remote GitHub repository
Option A: GitHub CLI
```powershell
gh repo create Coastal_Hazard --public --source . --remote origin --push
```

Option B: Web UI
1. Create new empty repo in GitHub.
2. Copy HTTPS URL.
3. Run:
```powershell
git remote add origin <YOUR_GITHUB_URL>
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
```

### 6.4 Ongoing workflow
```powershell
git status
git add .
git commit -m "Add improvement: <message>"
git push
```

